    "The only outlier in this regard is the animal class, which has a much higher scaffold diversity rate (51.3%).",
    "This behavior might be related to the low number of NPs annotated for this class, or to the presence of acyclic natural products (e.g.",
    "linear peptides), making the Murcko scaffolds not as informative.To compare the chemical space of NPs to typical druglike compounds, we also included the Drug Repurposing Hub library in our analysis [23].",
